  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "1997-02-13", 
    "text": "Crop Insurance Improvement Act of 1997 - Amends the Federal Crop Insurance Act to define \"designated disaster area\" to include an area: (1) declared a major disaster area by the President; or (2) determined to be a disaster area by the Secretary of Agriculture. Prohibits the Federal Crop Insurance Corporation from: (1) listing a producer with disaster-area crop losses on the nonstandard classification list; and (2) considering such losses in yield determinations."
  }, 
